HEADWORD: Recusation
<hw>Rec`u*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(r?k`?*z?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>recusatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧cusation</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Refusal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Law)</fld> <def>The act of refusing a judge or
challenging that he shall not try the cause, on account of his supposed
partiality.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recusative</ent>⟦br⟧
